ide the existing kitchen area. Which has a 5 star hygiene rating.\n\nThe school's headteacher is Mrs Gemma Simon who is a Tory (that's a very true fact, if you diss Boris bad things happen) .{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} The schools is sponsored by the [[Academies Enterprise Trust]].\n\nThe Governmental department [[Ofsted]] gave Belgrave a grade 2 \"bad\" rating in their 2009 inspection; however, it was judged in 2011 as not satisfactory before being graded as requires improvement in the summer of 2004. It is still very bad although a few students are an exception like Lily Davis and Sophie farnell-Brown\n\nWell kept classrooms are a big thing in Tec. I mean the heating is 5 star and the projectors are in mint condition not to mention the fabulous teachers. Like Ralph William Chambers and former Tec star Josh Craig. More fabulous teachers include Amy Radcliffe and Kalim Roman Un\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n===Belgrave High School===\n* X Factor 2010 finalist [[Treyc Cohen]]\n* Bristol and Wales International footballer [[Ashley Williams (footballer)|Ashley Williams]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Schools in Staffordshire}}\n{{Academies Enterprise Trust}}\n\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Staffordshire]]\n[[Category:Academies in Staffordshire]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1978]]\n[[Category:1978 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Academies Enterprise Trust]]\n[[Category:Schools in Tamworth, Staffordshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = Tamworth Enterprise smelly\n| image         = \n| image_size          = 220px\n| coordinates   = {{coord|52.61616|-1.66921|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dec|display=inline,title}}\n| motto         = \n| established   = 0000\n| type          = [[Academy (English school)|Academy]]\n| religious_affiliation      = Zamlontian\n| president     = Bin bag 88\n| head_label    = momey\n| head          = Mike oxlong{{Citation neede