{"title_page": "List of largest church buildings", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{merge from|List of tallest church buildings|date=September 2019}}\n{{more citations needed|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n[[File:Saint Peter's Basilica facade, Rome, Italy.jpg|thumb|[[St. Peter's Basilica]] in [[Vatican City]], the largest church in the world.]]\n\nA [[Church (building)|church]] can be measured by various criteria in order to determine its size. Such measures include area, volume, length, width, height, or capacity. Several churches individually claim to be \"the largest church\", which may be due to any one of these criteria.\n\nThis list includes extant churches that have a known area of more than {{convert|2000|m2}}. Entries are included even if they currently do not function as a church. For example, the [[Hagia Sophia]] is included\u2013 it was originally built as a church but was later converted into a mosque and is now a museum. Churches are not included if no reliable sources are available for their stated sizes.\n\n==List==\n{{Clear}}\n<!--\n* Please do not overload the column \"Comment\" with detailed descriptions that ought to be placed in the linked articles -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Name\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" colspan=2 | Area (m\u00b2)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" rowspan=2 | Gross volume (m\u00b3)\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" rowspan=2 | Capacity\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" rowspan=2 | Built\n! rowspan=2 | City\n! rowspan=2 | Country\n! rowspan=2 | Denomination\n! rowspan=2 class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n! Interior\n! Exterior\n|-\n|[[St. Peter's Basilica]]\n| 15,160<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://ar-tour.com/guides/rome-day-3/st-peters-basilica.aspx|title=Rome day 3|website=ar-tour.com|access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref>\n| 21,095<ref name=\":0\" />\n|\n|60,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.visual-arts-cork.com/history-of-art/saint-peters-basilica.htm|title=Saint Peter's Basilica, Rome: History, Architecture|website=www.visual-arts-cork.com|access-date=14 May 2019}}</ref>\n| 1506\u20131626 \n| [[Vatican City]]\n|{{Flag|Vatican City}}\n| [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] ([[Latin Church|Latin]])\n| \n|-\n|[[Basilica of the National Shrine of the Immaculate Conception]]\n|12,069<ref name=\"Basilica of NSOTIC\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nationalshrine.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/BNSIC-Architectural-Details-of-the-Basilica.pdf|title=Architectural Details of the Basilica|website=National Shrine of the Immaculate Conception|language=en-US|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n|\n| \n| 10,000\n| 1920\u20132017\n|[[Washington, DC]]\n|{{Flag|United States}}\n|[[Catholic Church|Catholic]] ([[Latin Church|Latin]])\n| Largest Catholic church in the United States and North America. The interior area refers to the lower floor (Crypt Church, Memorial Hall and facilities), which is partly below the ground level. The gross floor area of the upper floor and Great Upper Church is 7,097 m\u00b2, for a total gross floor area of 19,166 m\u00b2.<ref name=\"Basilica of NSOTIC\"></ref>\n|-\n|[[Basilica of the National Shrine of Our Lady of Aparecida]]\n| 12,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/the-largest-churches-in-the-world.html|title=The Biggest Churches in the World|website=WorldAtlas|language=en|access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themysteriousworld.com/10-largest-churches-in-the-world/|title=Top 10 Largest Churches in the World|date=26 November 2014|website=The Mysterious World|language=en-US|access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-pope-basilica-idUSN0236838720070506|title=Brazil's giant basilica is backdrop for Pope visit|date=6 May 2007|work=Reuters|access-date=12 November 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n|18,331<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.a12.com/santuario/santuario-em-numeros|title=Santu\u00e1rio em n\u00fameros - A12.com|website=www.a12.com|access-date=14 May 2019}}</ref>\n| 1,200,000<ref name=\"timesonline.co.uk\">{{cite news|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/comment/faith/article2641435.ece |title=Faith |work=Times Online|date=13 March 2012 |accessdate=5 September 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080830100755/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/comment/faith/article2641435.ece |archivedate=30 August 2008 }}</ref>\n|45,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/turismo/internacional/aparecida-e-basilica-de-s-pedro-veja-as-maiores-igrejas-do-mundo,d45691d8b1d1e310VgnVCM3000009acceb0aRCRD.html|title=Aparecida e Bas\u00edlica de S. Pedro; veja as maiores igrejas do mundo|website=Terra|language=pt-BR|access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref>\n| 1955\u201380\n| [[Aparecida]]\n|{{Flag|Brazil}}\n| [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] ([[Latin Church|Latin]])\n| \n|-\n|[[Seville Cathedral]]\n| 11,520<ref name=\"andalucia.com\">{{cite web |last=Quintero |first=Josephine |url=http://www.andalucia.com/cities/seville/cathedral.htm |title=Seville Cathedral, The City of Seville main sights, Andalucia, Southern Spain |publisher=Andalucia.com |accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref>\n|\n| 500,000 +\n| \n| 1401\u20131528\n| [[Seville]]\n|{{Flag|Spain}}\n| [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] ([[Latin Church|Latin]])\n| According to [[UNESCO]], the largest Gothic religious building.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catedraldesevilla.es/la-catedral/patrimonio-de-la-humanidad/|title=Patrimonio de La Humanidad |work= Catedral de Sevilla}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Milan Cathedral]]\n| 11,700<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.duomopatrons.org/it/infopage/i-numeri-del-duomo-di-milano/c669dfe2-3e8c-4398-b55c-cc4140b9a6c1/|title=I NUMERI DEL DUOMO DI MILANO|trans-title=The Numbers of the Duomo of Milan|publisher= International Patrons of Duomo of Milan|language=it}}</ref>\n|\n| 440,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ticketone.it/duomo-di-milano-biografia.html?doc=artistPag