ell's Cathedrals: The Cathedral Church of Winchester| url=https://www.gutenberg.org/files/20346/20346-h/20346-h.htm| first=Philip W.| last=Sergeant| publisher=George Bell & Sons| location=London| year=1899}}</ref>\n|\n|  \n|\n| 1079\u20131525 \n| [[Winchester]]\n|{{Flag|United Kingdom}}\n| [[Anglican Communion|Anglican]] ([[Church of England]]) \n| The longest Gothic Cathedral in Europe{{Citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n|-\n|[[Almudena Cathedral]]\n| 4,800{{Citation needed|date=December 2019}}\n|\n|  \n|\n| 1883\u20131993 \n| [[Madrid]]\n|{{Flag|Spain}}\n| [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] ([[Latin Church|Latin]]) \n| It has a North-South orientation instead of East-West.\n|-\n|[[Cathedral of Christ the Saviour]]\n| 3,990<ref name=\"\u0425\u0420\u0410\u041c \u0425\u0420\u0418\u0421\u0422\u0410 \u0421\u041f\u0410\u0421\u0418\u0422\u0415\u041b\u042f\">{{Cite web|url=http://new.xxc.ru/about/istoriya_hrama/istoriya/postroenie_hrama|title=\u0425\u0420\u0410\u041c \u0425\u0420\u0418\u0421\u0422\u0410 \u0421\u041f\u0410\u0421\u0418\u0422\u0415\u041b\u042f|website=new.xxc.ru|access-date=9 August 2019}}</ref>\n|6,829.3<ref name=\"\u0425\u0420\u0410\u041c \u0425\u0420\u0418\u0421\u0422\u0410 \u0421\u041f\u0410\u0421\u0418\u0422\u0415\u041b\u042f\"/>\n| 101 992<ref name=\"\u0425\u0420\u0410\u041c \u0425\u0420\u0418\u0421\u0422\u0410 \u0421\u041f\u0410\u0421\u0418\u0422\u0415\u041b\u042f\"/>\n|\n| 1839\u201383 \n| [[Moscow]] \n|{{Flag|Russia}}\n| [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodox]] ([[Russian Orthodox Church|Russian]]) \n| Rebuilt from 1995 to 2000\n|-\n|[[Dresden Cathedral]]\n| 4,800{{Citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n|\n|  \n|\n| 1739\u201355 \n| [[Dresden]]\n| {{Flag|Germany}} \n| [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] ([[Latin Church|Latin]]) \n| Largest church in all of Saxony{{Citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n|-\n|[[Basilica of St. Th\u00e9r\u00e8se, Lisieux]]\n| 4,500{{Citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n|\n|  \n|\n| 1929\u201354 \n| [[Lisieux]] \n| {{Flag|Fran