e Cathedral]]\n| 3,357<ref name=\"GC-Arch\">{{cite web |url=https://gracecathedral.org/architecture-2/ |title=Architecture |author=Lampen, Michael |website=Grace Cathedral |accessdate=22 April 2019}}</ref>\n|\n|  \n|\n| 1910\u201364 \n| [[San Francisco]]\n|{{Flag|United States}}\n|[[Anglican Communion|Anglican]] ([[Episcopal Church (United States)|Episcopal Church in the U.S.]])\n|\n|-\n|[[Basilica of Saints Peter and Paul (Lewiston, Maine)]]\n|3,264\n|\n|\n|2,200\n|1906\u20131936\n|[[Lewiston, Maine]]\n|{{Flag|United States}}\n|[[Catholic Church|Catholic]] ([[Latin Church|Latin]])\n|Largest church in the State of Maine, still serves mass in French.\n|-\n|[[Alexander Nevsky Cathedral, Sofia|Alexander Nevsky Cathedral]]\n| 3,170<ref>{{cite web|title=I love early morning Sofia|url=http://hitotoki.org/classic/sofia/004|quote=The church occupies an area of 3170 m\u00b2 and can accommodate up to 5,000 worshippers inside, which makes it the second biggest cathedral on the Balkan Peninsula after the Temple of Saint Sava in Serbia|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100330000719/http://hitotoki.org/classic/sofia/004|archivedate=30 March 2010|work=Hitotoki}}</ref>\n|\n| 86,000<ref>[http://15veka.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/ENG_PATRIARCHAL-CATHEDRAL-STAUROPIGIAL.pdf ''15 Century Bulgaria Foundation''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180425183233/http://15veka.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/ENG_PATRIARCHAL-CATHEDRAL-STAUROPIGIAL.pdf |date=25 April 2018 }} (15 \u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 \u0411\u042a\u041b\u0413\u0410\u0420\u0418\u042f) website, article with title ''Patriarchal cathedral stauropigial memorial church St. Alexander Nevsky'' (pdf)</ref>\n|\n| 1882\u20131912 \n| [[Sofia]] \n|{{Flag|Bulgaria}}\n| [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodox]] ([[Bulgarian Orthodox Church|Bulgaria]]) \n|\n|-\n|[[Crystal Cathedral]]\n|3,030<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.archdaily.com/445618/ad-classics-the-crystal-cathedral-philip-johnson |title=AD 